    "name": "Mad and Spectral",
    "profile": "Actually, this project was awaited logically...\r\nAfter numerous collaborations between these two artists – Mad Dee Jay and DJ Garry Spectrum, the consequence had to be a constant collaboration – a duo Mad and Spectral.\r\n\r\nThe production period of Mad and Spectral can be divided into two main parts: during the first one, the duo was concentrated on house, soulful and NY-deep production, and as a result the tracks such as \"Beautiful Dayz Of Our Life\", \"Funk Above\", \"Pop-Porn\", \"Le Plaisir Oceanique\" and \"Distant Starz\" were born. In the course of time, Mad and Spectral started to fuse and generate their main sound with the contemporary deep house and deep tech elements, shaping their trademark and recognizable sound.\r\n\r\nTunes such as \"Paradise\" (with Mad and Spectral's new discovery, female vocalist Lucia), as well as \"I_Love\", \"Nightlife\" and \"Let You Go\" blew the club charts and became the often guests of the various radio-shows and received dj-support from all over the world.\r\n\r\nIn th",
